[u'Financial Analyst
Beijing Wangfujing Group - Beijing
March 2014 to Present
To seek mergers and acquisitions opportunities in commercial projects and retail companies;
To collect and filter financial and operating information from investigated companies;
To prepare financial analysis reports of the investigated companies;
To collect monthly financial statements and operating information from subsidiaries and department stores;
To prepare monthly analysis reports of the parent company in terms of financial and operation performance;
To assist internal auditors in annual audit reports for the department stores.']

[u'Senior Financial Analyst
Laubannsteed, Inc
January 2013 to Present
• Evaluate financial aspects of product development; budgets, balance sheets, expenditures, allocations for research and development, projections for return on investment, and projects for profit and loss;
• Collaborate with finance leaders to create annual Operating Plans that align with strategic initiatives;
• Analyse markets, portfolio characteristics, investment styles, and associated performances each quarter;
• Prepare reports through analysis of client-specific investment data in support of colleagues;
• Utilize Bloomberg products to research market trends to stay current with regard to company placement,
marketing strategies, and budgeting;
• Facilitate all internal and external financial statement preparation needs;
• Assist in the analysis of monthly and quarterly financial reports, including variance analysis;
• Prepare supporting schedules and perform analytical test work for audit and other audit deliverables;
• Review and edit content for company reports, presentations and various communication initiatives;
• Identify positive and negative financial outcomes in order to determine most effective avenues to profitability;
• Initiate and confirm all arrangements for meetings including audio and video conference calls;
• Develop new analytical packages and drive improvements in overall FP&A processes in order to simplify and enhance the organization;
• Perform ad hoc analyses (e.g. deep dive cost studies and strategic business cases) that support management
in developing initiatives to drive growth and margin improvements;
• Process expense reports and counsel legal bills for payments through Concur and e-billing systems;', u'Financial Analyst
Laubannsteed, Inc
January 2011 to January 2013']

[u"Financial Analyst
Guardian Industries
August 2011 to October 2016
Financial Analyst at Guardian Industries Corp.
August 2015 - November 2016 (1 year 4 months)
*Treasury
Cash management functions including the daily settlement process, daily cash management
reporting, reconciliations, and journal entries;
Maintain bank account, cash, investments, collections, debt and interest schedule;
Support cash forecasting process and contribute to the global management strategy;
Ensure accurate maintenance of bank accounts (6 national and 4 foreign accounts) including
balance, bank systems, inclusion and approval of payments, bank fees analysis bank cost
information;
Banking relationships including authorizations, reconciliations, evaluation of new banking products
and services and ensuring adequate liquidity is available;
Inspect, investigate and resolve discrepancies for all treasury related transactions;
Analyze and manage all aspects of the company's cash flow;
Maintain, and manage appropriate treasury and accounting procedures and processes.
Control guarantees, letters of credit and loan agreements;
Analyze, prepare, execute foreign exchange transactions (suppliers payments, loan payments,
foreign collections). Foreign exchange transactions for Mexico, Venezuela, and Costa Rica plants;
Perform other tasks that may be assigned by the Fin. Manager and Controller;
Maintain current knowledge of all Fed. and State Laws and Regulations, along with all the
company's policies and procedures;
Support for Audits (Internal and External);

Assist and support other financial staff in:

*Accounts Receivable (Includes training a new Accts Rec. Analyst for a new plant)
Post of incoming payments to customer accounts; analyzing payment discrepancies and balances;
work closely with Sales and Credit Dept; provide accurate customer credit, collections and financial
records report for coordinator and managers and customers.

*Accounts Payable (Backup and Daily Support)
Encompasses the entire accounts payable cycle ensuring on-time payments certifying appropriate
documentation for invoices, expense reports, and advanced payments.

